The paper deals with hyperparameter optimization for machine learning models, specifically for image classification using a convolutional neural network. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks for image classification suggests the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method proposed in the paper involves optimizing hyperparameters for multiple tasks, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of multicriteria optimization could also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
